---
import { Bullets } from '~/components/Bullets';
import { Button } from '~/components/Button';
import { CalloutCard } from '~/components/CalloutCard';
import { DraftModeQueryListener } from '~/components/DraftModeQueryListener';
import { Flag } from '~/components/Flag';
import { Hero } from '~/components/Hero';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { Layout } from '~/layouts/Layout';
import { SingleQuote } from '~/components/quote/SingleQuote';
import { Space } from '~/components/Space';
import { Svg } from '~/components/Svg';
import { TitleStripWithContent } from '~/components/TitleStripWithContent';
import { Wrapper } from '~/components/Wrapper';
import { avoidAstroTypeCheckBug, notFoundResponse } from '~/lib/notFoundResponse';
import { executeQuery } from '~/lib/datocms/executeQuery';
import { query } from './_graphql';
import s from './_style.module.css';
import { overrideSeo, seoDescription, seoGeneratedCard, seoTitle } from '~/lib/datocms/seo';

const variables = { slug: Astro.url.pathname.split('/').pop()! };
const { page } = await executeQuery(Astro, query, { variables });

if (!page) {
  avoidAstroTypeCheckBug(notFoundResponse);
  return notFoundResponse();
}
---

<Layout
  seo={overrideSeo(
    page._seoMetaTags,
    seoTitle('DatoCMS MCP Beta'),
    seoDescription(
      'LLM-friendly. Token Hungry. 6 months and 3 rewrites later, the DatoCMS MCP Beta is here.',
    ),
    seoGeneratedCard(Astro, {
      title: 'DatoCMS MCP Beta',
      excerpt:
        'LLM-friendly. Token Hungry. 6 months and 3 rewrites later, the DatoCMS MCP Beta is here.',
    }),
  )}
>
  <Hero>
    <Fragment slot="kicker">DatoCMS MCP (Beta)</Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="title">
      LLM-friendly. Token Hungry. <mark>NotTheWorst</mark>™
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      6 months and 3 rewrites later, the DatoCMS MCP Beta is here. Not because its perfect, but
      because it needs work.
    </Fragment>
    <div class={s.buttonContainer}>
      <Button fs="big" as="a" href="https://github.com/datocms/mcp">Check the repo</Button>
      <Button fs="big" as="a" s="invert" href="/blog/we-have-released-an-mcp-sometimes-it-works"
        >Learn more</Button
      >
    </div>
  </Hero>

  <Flag>
    <Fragment slot="visual">
      <Image
        src="https://www.datocms-assets.com/205/1761921587-logs.png"
        inferSize
        alt="Deterministic"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
      />
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="kicker"> We built an MCP </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="title"> It works. Terms & Conditions Apply. </Fragment>
    <p>
      We built the MCP to run through discovery, planning, and execution, using scripts,
      documentation, and actual reasoning.
    </p>
    <p>While its in Beta, it’s slow, token-hungry, and unpredictable, but it gets things done.</p>
  </Flag>

  <Space top={1} bottom={3}>
    <Wrapper>
      <CalloutCard
        title="Works with what you're used to"
        ctaLink="https://github.com/datocms/mcp?tab=readme-ov-file#datocms-mcp"
        ctaLabel="Get started →"
        illustration="svg/illustrations/live-4"
        asLink
      >
        <Fragment slot="text">
          We've tested the MCP most with Claude Code and Cursor, but you can get it up and running
          with any tool you're used to like Gemini CLI, VS Code, and Windsurf, using the standard
          config.
        </Fragment>
      </CalloutCard>
    </Wrapper>
  </Space>

  <Flag>
    <Fragment slot="visual">
      <Image
        src="https://www.datocms-assets.com/205/1761921589-deterministic.png"
        inferSize
        alt="Deterministic"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
      />
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="kicker"> How we built it </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="title"> Our approach to the MCP </Fragment>
    <p>
      Rather than throwing endpoints against the wall, we've taken a carefully layered approach.
    </p>
    <article>
      <Bullets style="good">
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>A local MCP server for the DatoCMS API</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>10 carefully layered tools, not 150+ raw endpoints</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Script-based reasoning, not single call guessing</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Documentation- and schema-aware</span>
        </li>
      </Bullets>
    </article>
  </Flag>

  <Space bottom={3}>
    <TitleStripWithContent stripHeight="full">
      <Fragment slot="kicker"> Take it for a spin </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="title"> Here's where you come in </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="subtitle">
        Its not perfect, but while MCP standards are still forming, we'd love real world feedback
        from your usage to help us make it better.
      </Fragment>
      <div class={s.buttonContainer}>
        <Button fs="big" as="a" href="https://github.com/datocms/mcp">Check the repo</Button>
        <Button fs="big" as="a" s="invert" href="/blog/we-have-released-an-mcp-sometimes-it-works"
          >Learn more</Button
        >
      </div>
    </TitleStripWithContent>
  </Space>

  <Flag>
    <Fragment slot="visual">
      <Image
        src="https://www.datocms-assets.com/205/1761921589-integrate.png"
        inferSize
        alt="Integrate"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
      />
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="kicker"> Here's what it does really well </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="title"> The Capabilities </Fragment>
    <article>
      <Bullets style="good">
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Generate new records, and translate content well</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Correctly modify model and field settings</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Run structured and chained batch operations with TypeScript scripts</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Fetch docs for context before attempting calls</span>
        </li>
      </Bullets>
    </article>
  </Flag>

  <Flag>
    <Fragment slot="visual">
      <Image
        src="https://www.datocms-assets.com/205/1761921589-integrate.png"
        inferSize
        alt="Integrate"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
      />
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="kicker"> Here's where it struggles </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="title"> The Limitations </Fragment>
    <article>
      <Bullets style="bad">
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/toilet-paper-alt" />
          <span>Its slow. Discovery and planning takes time.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/toilet-paper-alt" />
          <span>Its hungry. Docs lookups eat up context and tokens.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/toilet-paper-alt" />
          <span>Its unpredictable. It may take weird approaches.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/toilet-paper-alt" />
          <span>Its not scalable (yet). Big operations can time out.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/toilet-paper-alt" />
          <span>Its you. Your model and prompt style matter. A LOT.</span>
        </li>
      </Bullets>
    </article>
  </Flag>

  <Flag>
    <Fragment slot="visual">
      <Image
        src="https://www.datocms-assets.com/205/1761921587-logs.png"
        inferSize
        alt="Deterministic"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
      />
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="kicker"> What you can expect </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="title"> What's in the box? </Fragment>
    <p>If you take the MCP out for a spin, here's what you get</p>
    <article>
      <Bullets style="good">
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span
            >10 carefully crafted tools with full script lifecycle for creates, edits, views, and
            runs.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Schema introspection, TypeScript, AST Validation, and secure sandboxing</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Works with Claude, Cursor, VS Code, and more.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Svg name="icons/regular/check" />
          <span>Token vs. No-token modes with helpful docs.</span>
        </li>
      </Bullets>
    </article>
  </Flag>

  {
    page.quote && (
      <Wrapper>
        <Space top={3} bottom={3}>
          <SingleQuote quote={page.quote} />
        </Space>
      </Wrapper>
    )
  }

  <DraftModeQueryListener query={query} variables={variables} />
</Layout>
